  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring Vulnerable Migrants&#x2019; Access to Mental Health Support and Other Essential Disaster Management Services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the context of COVID-19 and recurrent hurricanes and future disaster risks, this project improves vulnerable migrants&#x2019; access to and participation in essential disaster management systems in the Bahamas, with a particular emphasis on access to mental health and psychosocial support services (MPHSS). This is done by addressing &#x201C;trust gaps&#x201D; and modelling a collaboration and constructive engagement culture between eight migrant communities in New Providence, Abaco and Eleuthera, the International Organization for Migration (IOM) and key Bahamian governmental agencies (The National Emergency Management Agency, The Department of Gender and Family Affairs) and civil society agencies such as the Bahamas Psychological Association (BPA).The project aims to build the capacity of these agencies and implement community risk assessments and disaster risk reduction activities.</narrative>
  </description>
